(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Ottawa - A 35-year-old male suspect was arrested on Thursday in connection with an apparent crossbow attack outside Toronto, police said.Police said officers responding to an emergency call found three deceased people on a residential street, on the east side of Canada's largest metropolis.Nearby, police also found a crossbow. Authorities said, however, that it was not immediately clear that the weapon had been used in the attack.Paramedics said the three victims, two men and a woman appear to have died from "blunt force" trauma. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.